Supports section: fix orchestrator logos + table copy (Antigravity, Grok Build, Monitor→Support)


## Problem
Homepage Supports section (`#supports`) has wrong logos and several copy/structure issues.

### Logos (current monochrome placeholders are wrong)
| Agent | Issue / correct source |
|-------|------------------------|
| **Claude Code** | Icon is wrong |
| **Grok** | Icon is wrong — use official mark from **grok.com** |
| **Pi** | Icon is wrong — use official mark from **pi.dev** |
| **OpenCode** | Icon is wrong — search web for official/brand mark |
| **Codex** | Icon is wrong — search web for official OpenAI Codex mark |
| **Antigravity** | Icon is wrong — search web for official Google Antigravity mark |

Replace assets under `site/assets/logos/` (or equivalent). Prefer local SVGs, dark-bg friendly, correct brand recognition, alt text. Respect trademark/brand guidelines (simple official monochrome or simplified marks as allowed).

### Table / strip copy & order
1. **Antigravity higher in the list** — among primary orchestrators (not last/muted).
2. **Name:** **Antigravity** only — do **not** show “agy” / aka / logo-strip hint.
3. **Grok row:** **“Grok Build”** only (no “/ Grok CLI”).
4. **Antigravity notes:** remove “see B049 / docs” and similar internal refs.
5. **Column rename:** Monitor → **Support**.
6. **Support cell values:**
   - Claude Code, Grok Build: **`Native / Monitor`**
   - Antigravity: **`Native / AgentAPI`**
7. **Pi & OpenCode:** frame our plugins as **examples** of Monitor plugins — any plugin offering Monitor on `hark monitor --for-monitor` works equally well.

### Acceptance
- [ ] Logos match recognizable official marks for listed agents
- [ ] Antigravity order among primary tier; no “agy” in UI
- [ ] “Grok Build” only; Support column + Native/Monitor & Native/AgentAPI wording
- [ ] Pi/OpenCode notes are example-plugins, not exclusive
- [ ] No backlog IDs in marketing copy; CHANGELOG + visual check

### Files
- `site/index.html` (`#supports`), `site/assets/logos/*`, CSS as needed
- CLI binary name `agy` may remain in `docs/AGY.md` only